name: spint
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "spint" %}
{% set version = "1.0.7" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/spint-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7ee6bfc725f8b507abd43f3d397bde8eaf6d85b8052f9ecb0c69f613bfeac4ca

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - libpysal >=4.0.0
    - numpy >=1.3
    - scipy >=0.11
    - spglm >=1.0.6
    - spreg

test:
  imports:
    - spint
    - spint.tests
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: http://pysal.org/
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: 'Efficient calibration of spatial interaction models in Python'

  description: |
    The Spatial Interaction Modeling (SpInt) module provides a collection of
    tools to study spatial interaction processes and analyze spatial
    interaction data.
  doc_url: http://readthedocs.org/projects/spint
  dev_url: http://github.com/pysal/spint

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - TaylorOshan
    - ocefpaf
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
